if you want to allow input in a single line (like "1 2 3"), you can slightly modify the code like this

n = int(input())
num = list(map(int, input().split()))  # takes all elements in one line
print(num)




3
1 2 3
 For float (Decimal Numbers)

numbers = list(map(float, input().split()))




For Custom Functions

You can also use your own custom functions with map().
Example:

If you want to take inputs and calculate their squares:


def square(x):
    return int(x) ** 2

squares = list(map(square, input().split()))








